{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6556e5d8-6bad-4b9c-9092-ef0788abc34c","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_HHgR7X3ktCd3Mf7HTcMxvU","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-61cf61ef34664fd69425ec26165685dd/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-61cf61ef34664fd69425ec26165685dd/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"29a98621-d10d-47d4-8913-32db4ece8cb1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), and `Program.fs` depends on both. So the correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` first (no dependencies)\n2. `Services.fs` second (depends on Domain)\n\n\n3. `Program.fs` third (depends on Domain and Services)\n\nI need to reorder these files in the `.fsproj` to fix the compilation error.","outputTokens":474,"requestId":"1917:142AE8:12BE776:151A955:6A066E93"},"id":"a92e8e0b-a87d-410e-851f-0068f2900b28","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:48.198Z","parentId":"33275f98-ab42-4a2d-a7d6-3b6bca9465da"}
